<br>
I've never mentioned a guild name here, and dont have any intention to.  I do my best not to judge people by their guildtag, but in the manner they present themselves.<br>
<br>
As for this issue, it isnt about anyone that's already here.  That's another subject entirely.  Its about the people that want to come here and who, honestly, shouldnt be allowed in my opinion.<br>
<br>
The rules were changed without any notification.  Can SOE do that?  Sure.  Should they?  I dont think so.  As a customer, it upsets me and I mean to tell them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why not? This is still unclear. The &quot;roleplaying preferred&quot; tag isn't a sufficient argument.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That statement, however, is the problem.  It's not a point I plan on budging on, and isnt really something either of us can argue.<br>
<br>
As it stands though, it doesnt matter.  Nothing said in this forum or on this board really makes much difference.  In the end, and in the game, things will continue on as usual.<br>
<br>
Its better that way really.  This place is much &quot;louder&quot; at times then it needs to be.  I contribute to that on some issues, so I suppose your definition of &quot;hypocrite&quot; does define me in some ways.<br>
<br>
You DO have every right to come onto FV and not roleplay one bit.  You can even yell at those that do and mock them.  You shouldnt, but I suppose thats not the issue and I doubt it ever will be.<br>
<br>
Enjoy your time in game. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~Vabris Vy'Tok, of House Vy'Tok~<br>
