<br>
How about a direct way this affects those who have been here, not on the fast track, but smelling the roses along the way.  Epics and gear.  <br>
<br>
The transfers are &quot;naked&quot;, no gear.  Where are they going to get the gear and quickly so they can get back into their elemetal planes and other such.  <br>
<br>
Cleric epic is a very nice clicky rez, let's use it as an example since I'll bet a 65 with buckets of AA cleric coming here is going to want to have that again.  So, he then monopolises the spawns relating to his epic while organisations such as the Fellowship are also trying to hit those same targets.  The big bottle neck of old is now triggered, but if you look back a year ago you will find Blaeze fighting with the high end guilds to try to get that target for his epic (and the fact he didn't at that time ).  We will have this in spades with transfers if there are many of them.  <br>
<br>
Other gear will be farmed in places the RP guilds and associations are now reaching the ability to take and are using to gear up their own members (many of them having been here from day one):  HoT, Kael, Umbral Plains, etc.  So yes, it does affect us, the smaller guild, the roleplay guilds.  <br>
<br>
The other way the transfers will gear up will be by using plat bought with their visa or mastercard from Exxy and the like who will continue to use exploits to generate plat to sell.  This will in turn trigger more nerfs on those things that can turn a tiny profit for the one not using the exploits because they can generate huge profits for those exploiting (for a reference here... fletching.  ONE arrow with a triv of 202 began to pay off enough to offset costs to make and a margin for failures at about 187 or 189 skill.  They not only made the buy back of the arrow less than it's parts, which I agree with because of the macro-ers, they also nerfed fletching skill-ups and success rate to an extremely extremely low rate.  As a direct response to the plat machine of the macro-ers).  Yes, this will trickle down, in plat, to some of those &quot;legitimately&quot; selling gear but will be more likely to end up lining the pockets of the Exxy-bots since they are selling the No Drop everywhere else high-end gear.<br>
<br>
But oh, that's right, we're doomsayers because it won't do anything but benefit the high end raiding guilds who see the 65 with buckets of AA as the true marks of a person.  <br>
<br>
At Fan Faire, people would introduce themselves with level and AAs.  I couldn't help but think how much nicer on FV where those are not the prime thing those of this server look to.  But... now... isn't this one way we have become identical to the other servers?  or at least those who are in the &quot;high-end&quot;.<br>
