<br>
Before you say anything, yes, I am a meber of FnF and thus spend most of my time raiding.  I also consider myself to be a decent roleplayer.  Maybe not the best, but I have my story, some friends to chat with IC, and tells/channels to do it in, and I enjoy myself while doing so, so I figure I'm well off in that regard.  (Heaven forbid someone should try to do both, I know.)<br>
<br>
I'm going to pick apart some posts, I think.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Rules don't make a server RP, people make the server RP. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First bit of intelligence I've seen in this thread.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Where are they going to get the gear and quickly so they can get back into their elemetal planes and other such.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
How is this different from competition with any other group of players capable of taking down said target?  Can't do much about the RL cash argument.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>the high end raiding guilds who see the 65 with buckets of AA as the true marks of a person.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Overgeneralizing is a bad thing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's not the roleplayers training people during city raids, and its not the roleplayers crowding up shout with inane horse shit every hour of the night in POK. You want to start point fingers?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hate to tell you, those people were here without transferring.  And there's no evidence to show that newly transfered players will be like that.  As for the argument about tranferring only to be uber... I really don't see it.  When you look in the bazaar, do you see tons of Emperor, Cursed, VT, PoP god, Elemental gear?  No.  You know why?  The only sources for it are people ebaying out of FnF/Reso and selling to whomever.  And when those things in bazaar run out, then what?  To get a good amount of such gear takes quite a while, especially with lengthy app periods, etc., and once Shanana/Boog's stock runs out, there is no more.  People being motivated by greed to be uber aren't going to be as likely to come as you think... they want elemental armor and top of the line weapons which won't be for sale.  Your primal, NToV loot, Rhag loot... that's junk the top end.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The real problem is if this server is thrown wide open to transfers in you;ll be seeing entire guilds comming here enmass<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
See above.  No guild wants to buy crap gear and start over from Velious content except in the most extreme circumstances.  A comment was made about Maelin server.. if I remember correctly, transfers to MS were WITH GEAR.  There's a difference.  I'd be willing to wager that people wouldn't ever consider it if naysayers like you don't go putting ideas into their heads.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The day that some random d00d walks up to me and says &quot;d00d, WTF @re you s@ying, w/ teh 'th33z' and 'th0uz'? tak N0rmal, liek m3 LOL!!1!&quot; Is the day that I unleash my unholy wrath.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Amen.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why pick the ONE that is marked Roleplay Prefered if you have ZERO intention of roleplaying?<br>
<br>
Because you can? Then you're an asshole. That's an old issue though, and you know... there are some real nice people on FV that dont roleplay. That's fine, and I can appreciate them and their &quot;right&quot; to play here. Dont take this the wrong way, I dont bother people who dont roleplay if they dont bother me.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Anyone else notice a massive contradiction here???  &quot;Don't come if you have no intention of RPing.  But, people I know here, who don't RP, are ok, because they're my friends.  And hi, I'm a hypocrite!&quot;  Nonroleplayer doesn't necessarily mean d00d!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>When that community becomes so stressed out and so disgusted with the dredges that are being encouraging to come to this server, then they will quit.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Oh yes, the dregs of all the other servers are coming to the roleplay server, solely to diss roleplayers!  Sorry, if someone who was a total jerk came over, they wouldn't get in any guilds.  I can assure you, that if someone came who played 20 hours a day, was incredible at their class, and had every aa trained, yet quickly proved they were an asshole, talked only in dewdspeek, and trained/ks people repeatedly while applying, they wouldn't be accepted into FnF.  There would be far, far too many people offended, ya know?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Oh shit. There goes the neighborhood.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Kudos to Kuladen for the first documented Spaceballs picture in the soapbox!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As has been pointed in this thread having to level up under our rules has been a major deterrent to others comming here.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't see it, really.  May 8 removed all the deterrents.  Levels are so easy to make now... as I alluded to previously, it's the gear that's the deterrent, losing all of it and having to start over.  THAT is what consumes so much time.  All the flags and keys in the world do you no good when you can't kill a damn thing.  And ask any raider.. acquisition of the best raid-level gear takes a long, long time.<br>
<br>
Allright, that's enough for now.  I of course would appreciate some well thought out responses, but hell it's the soapbox.. flame away! <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/Rhatha_sig.jpg" style="border:0;height:270;width:399;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438">Elder Rhatha Sha`Naya</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and Swiftclaw<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fireandfury.org"><br>
